<HL>
   Who's News:
   Kalinske Resigns Post
   At Universal Matchbox
</HL>
<DATE>
09/25/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   UMG WNEWS
</CO>
<IN>
RECREATION, ENTERTAINMENT, TOYS, MOVIES, PHOTOGRAPHY, SPORTS (REC)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- Universal Matchbox Group Ltd., shedding a
layer of management, said Thomas J. Kalinske, 46-year-old
president and chief executive officer of its Matchbox
International Ltd. unit, has resigned to pursue other
interests.
   His resignation is effective Monday. As a result, managers
of its international toy businesses, which were under Mr.
Kalinske's direction, will report directly to David C.W. Yeh,
chairman and chief executive officer of the parent, based in
Hong Kong.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company said the resignation and realignment of
management are part of Matchbox's continuing efforts to
streamline its operations.
   The toy maker, known for its die-cast replica cars, also
said Kenneth Bloom, chief financial officer of Matchbox
International, was named executive vice president and general
manager of Matchbox Toys Ltd., in Moonachie, N.J.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
