   Business Brief -- Philadelphia Electric Co.:
   Company Expects to Take
   A Charge Against Earnings
</HL>
<DATE>
09/25/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C5
</SO>
<CO>
   PE LABOR
</CO>
<IN>
ELECTRIC UTILITIES (ELC)
</IN>
<LP>
   Philadelphia Electric Co. said it expects to take a
one-time charge of $249 million, or 70 cents a share, against
third-quarter earnings to reflect the cost of an early
retirement program.
   The utility said that 1,909 of its 11,273 employees, or
73% of those eligible, decided to take early retirement under
the plan, announced this summer.
</LP>
