<LP>
   NEW YORK -- American Telephone &amp; Telegraph Co. said it
will lower the price of calls to Canada from the U.S. under
its "Reach Out World" plan by 10%, beginning Oct. 5.
   The company said the reduction is pending regulatory
approval. Each call will cost 18 cents per minute for the
first 10 minutes. After 10 minutes, the price will be reduced
an additional 5%. The plan applies to calls made between 5
p.m. and 8 a.m. each weekday and all weekend.
